label.value: American College of Medical Genetics and Genomics

value.value: A nationally recognized interdisciplinary professional membership organization that represents the interests of the entire medical genetics field including clinical geneticists, clinical laboratory geneticists, and genetic counselors. The ACMG and its members engage in coordinated efforts to improve patient care, ensure optimal reimbursement for genetic service providers, establish standards of care and laboratory policy, and educate members about advances important to their practices. (https://www.acmg.net/)

label.value: HSV-Tk Gene

value.value: Herpes simplex virus thymidine kinase (HSV-Tk) gene encodes thymidine kinase protein, which is important for herpes simplex virus infection. The TK gene and promoter are widely used in genetic research because of the easily selectable phenotype.

label.value: Cellular Retinoic Acid Binding Protein

value.value: Cellular Retinoic Acid-Binding Proteins are assumed to play an important role in retinoic acid-mediated differentiation and proliferation processes.  Cytoplasmic CRABP-I and CRABP-II may regulate access of retinoic acid to nuclear retinoic acid receptors.  CRABP-II may participate in a regulatory feedback mechanism to control the action of retinoic acid on cell differentiation.  CRABP-I and CRABP-II belong to the FABP/P2/CRBP/CRABP family of transporters.  (from OMIM 180230, 180231, SWISS-PROT P29762, P29373, and NCI)

label.value: cDNA Array

value.value: A molecular biology device that utilizes a set of defined cDNA clones attached in a specific grid arrangement to a solid support for nucleic acid hybridization assays in gene mapping studies or in determining gene sequences, sequence variations, or gene expression patterns.

label.value: Residual Tumor Size Measurement

value.value: A procedure that measures the size of a residual tumor mass.

label.value: Risk Factor Diagnostic Method

value.value: The modality that was used to determine the presence and identity of a risk factor.

label.value: Number of Disease-Involved Anatomic Sites

value.value: The number of anatomic sites found to be involved in the disease.

label.value: Therapeutic Agent Level Achieved Indicator

value.value: An indication that the intended level of therapeutic agent was achieved in an individual.

label.value: Test Value Percent Range

value.value: The range of percent values in which an individual's test result values fell.

label.value: Autologous Dinitrophenyl Vaccine

value.value: A vaccine consisting of autologous cancer cells modified with the hapten, Dinitrophenyl. The treatment program consists of multiple intradermal injections of irradiated DNP-modified autologous tumor cells mixed with bacillus Calmette-Guerin.

label.value: Warburg Effect

value.value: This effect refers to the high cellular levels of lactic acid in tumor cells, and is named after Otto Warburg who worked on photosynthesis.  Tumor cells use excessive glucose in their rapid growth, and lactic acid is a product of the glycolytic pathway.  This process is not inhibited by oxygen, therefore, it is also called aerobic glycolysis.

label.value: Therapeutic Agent Targeted Administration Concentration

value.value: The intended concentration for administration of the therapeutic agent.

label.value: Timepoint Event Category

value.value: The classification or description of an event that is observed or recorded during a clinical encounter where a treatment is administered, a sample is collected for laboratory or molecular analysis or follow-up information is gathered.

label.value: Treatment Duration in Days

value.value: The number of days during which a treatment was administered to an individual.

label.value: Number of Elapsed Days Between Treatment and Outcome

value.value: The elapsed number of days between treatment completion and the occurrence of specific result or effect.

label.value: Tumor Grade Evaluation Tier Number

value.value: The number of clinical observation tiers used in the evaluation of the tumor grade.

label.value: Prostate Level Disease Origin Indicator

value.value: An indication that the apex, middle or base of the prostate was identified as the origin of the disease.

label.value: UICC Staging System Manual

value.value: The criteria developed by the Union for International Cancer Control (UICC) for the classification and staging of neoplastic diseases.

label.value: Substance Use Per Day

value.value: A question regarding the average number of times per day that an individual uses a substance of interest.

label.value: Year of Last Follow Up

value.value: The four digit year associated with the last clinical follow up.

label.value: CpG Island Methylator Phenotype

value.value: A phenotype whereby a subset of tumors are characterized by the simultaneous hypermethylation of multiple promoter-associated CpG islands.

label.value: Nerve Growth Factor Beta Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of nerve growth factor beta present in a sample.

label.value: Day Times Nanogram Per Milliliter Per Milligram Per Kilogram

value.value: Days times nanograms per milliliter (area under the curve), divided by milligrams per kilogram (dose normalized by body weight).

label.value: Distribution Pattern Finding Description

value.value: Description of the distribution pattern of a finding within the examined area.

label.value: Pruritus Indicator

value.value: An indicator as to whether the subject has symptoms of itchiness.

label.value: Escherichia coli Serogroup O157 Not Including H7 Serotype

value.value: Any bacterial organism that can be assigned to the species Escherichia coli and serogroup O157, but does not include the H7 serotype.
